---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Claude CLI vs API" section="claude-cli-vs-api">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">AI · Decision Framework</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">When to use CLI, <em>when to use API.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Claude Code (CLI), Claude.ai chat, and the Anthropic API are different tools for different jobs. Most marketing work happens in CLI for the first 30 days — the API only matters once a workflow needs to run autonomously or across a team.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="claude-cli-vs-api"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Progress: <span data-progress-here="claude-cli-vs-api">0 / 0</span></p>

  <!-- THREE SURFACES -->
  <h2>Three surfaces — <em>what they are.</em></h2>
  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Surface 1</span>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0">Claude.ai chat</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Browser interface at claude.ai. Conversational, single-user, fast. <strong>Projects</strong> let you pin docs as persistent context. Best for: research, drafting, brainstorming, "give me 10 versions of this headline."</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">$20/mo Pro · $30/mo Max · $200/mo Max with priority</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Surface 2</span>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0">Claude Code (CLI)</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Terminal-based agentic Claude. Runs locally, reads your filesystem, executes commands, edits files, runs scripts. <strong>What you're using right now to build this hub.</strong> Best for: building workflows, running scripts, multi-step automation that you supervise.</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Pro/Max plans · or pay-as-you-go via API key</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Surface 3</span>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0">Anthropic API</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Direct programmatic access. n8n / Python / your code calls it. Async, scheduled, scalable. <strong>Prompt caching</strong>, <strong>Batch API</strong>, <strong>MCP servers</strong>. Best for: production workflows, team automations, scheduled jobs.</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">$3/$15 per M tokens Sonnet · $15/$75 Opus</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- DECISION FRAMEWORK -->
  <h2>The decision framework</h2>
  <div class="callout">
    <div class="lbl">Single question that picks the surface</div>
    <p style="font-size:1.1rem"><strong>"Does this need to run when I'm not at the keyboard?"</strong></p>
    <p style="font-size:0.95rem;margin-top:0.5rem">No → <strong>Claude.ai chat or Claude Code (CLI)</strong>. Yes → <strong>Anthropic API</strong> (via n8n or custom code).</p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Use Claude.ai chat when</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>You're researching a topic (brainstorm, summarize web content)</li>
        <li>You want to draft something one-off (headline, email, blog post)</li>
        <li>You want to iterate conversationally ("now make it shorter," "now angrier")</li>
        <li>You're sharing screenshots/PDFs and asking questions about them</li>
        <li>You want to project-ify a knowledge base (pin 5-10 brand docs in a Project, ask questions)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Use Claude Code (CLI) when</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>You need Claude to <strong>read or edit local files</strong> (think: 47 brand docs in a folder)</li>
        <li>You need Claude to <strong>run shell commands</strong> (curl, jq, npm scripts, git)</li>
        <li>You're <strong>building or prototyping a workflow</strong> before automating it</li>
        <li>You're doing <strong>research that requires WebFetch / WebSearch</strong> at agentic depth</li>
        <li>You want a <strong>session that compounds</strong> — multiple tasks in one context, files persisted</li>
        <li>You want <strong>parallel subagents</strong> running research while you work</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Use Anthropic API when</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>The workflow needs to <strong>run on a schedule</strong> (nightly comp-intel, daily AEO check)</li>
        <li>The workflow runs <strong>multiple times per day, triggered by events</strong> (lead enrichment, battle cards)</li>
        <li><strong>Multiple team members</strong> need to use it without you in the loop</li>
        <li>You're processing <strong>large batches</strong> (5K practice personalization → Batch API)</li>
        <li>You need <strong>prompt caching</strong> economics (same context, many queries)</li>
        <li>The output goes into <strong>another system</strong> (Pardot, Salesforce, Slack)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Combine all three when</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li><strong>Day 1-7:</strong> Use Claude.ai chat to explore the problem</li>
        <li><strong>Day 7-30:</strong> Use Claude Code to prototype the workflow against real data</li>
        <li><strong>Day 30+:</strong> Hand the workflow to n8n + API for autonomous operation</li>
        <li>This is exactly how the 8 workflow recipes were designed</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SPECIFIC USE CASES MAPPED -->
  <h2>Use cases mapped — <em>what fits where.</em></h2>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Marketing task</th><th>Best surface</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Daily AEO monitoring across ChatGPT, Perplexity</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">API</span></td><td>Needs to run autonomously every morning. n8n + Otterly. You don't touch it.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>"Write me 10 LinkedIn post variants on PPO write-offs"</td><td><span class="pill pill-mint">Chat</span></td><td>One-off, conversational, you'll pick the best one.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Personalizing outreach for 5,000 practices</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">API (Batch)</span></td><td>Scale demands Batch API + Clay enrichment. Chat can't do 5K rows.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Researching what BoomCloud's Patient Marketplace actually does</td><td><span class="pill pill-green">CLI</span></td><td>WebFetch + multiple URLs + synthesis + file output. Chat can't fetch web at depth. CLI agentic flow finishes in 10 minutes.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Drafting a case study from a customer interview transcript</td><td><span class="pill pill-green">CLI (manual) or API (scaled)</span></td><td>Day 1: CLI does it. Workflow D: API runs it on every new transcript.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Sales battle card on demand</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">API</span></td><td>Sales reps trigger via Slack, not by asking you. API + MCP servers.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>"What questions should I ask Jim in our first 1:1?"</td><td><span class="pill pill-mint">Chat</span></td><td>Strategic brainstorm. Single session.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Auditing the 47 Notion docs in marketing folder</td><td><span class="pill pill-green">CLI</span></td><td>Reads filesystem (export Notion to markdown first), processes all of them in one pass. Chat can't read your filesystem.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Refreshing 30 press releases for AEO project</td><td><span class="pill pill-green">CLI then API</span></td><td>CLI does first 3-5 to nail the pattern. API runs the remaining 25 in Batch.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Weekly competitive intelligence digest</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">API</span></td><td>Monday 8am autonomous. n8n + Visualping + Claude. You read the Slack post.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Drafting your monthly Charlesbank board update</td><td><span class="pill pill-mint">Chat</span></td><td>You'll iterate 5-10x with judgment. Pin board template in a Project.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Personalized assets for each Clerri-member practice</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">API (Batch)</span></td><td>Scale + prompt caching economics. Workflow C.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>"Find every mention of Clerri on LinkedIn this week"</td><td><span class="pill pill-green">CLI</span></td><td>Agentic search + synthesis + ranked output. CLI subagents handle this.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Generating localized landing pages for 50 metro areas</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">API (Batch)</span></td><td>50 pages × consistent template = Batch API job. CLI prototypes first.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>"Critique this email I'm about to send to Jim"</td><td><span class="pill pill-mint">Chat</span></td><td>One-off, judgment-laden, no automation.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- CLI POWER MOVES -->
  <h2>Claude Code (CLI) power moves you should know</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">Claude Code is the most under-leveraged tool in your stack. Most marketers don't know it exists. These are the things it does that nothing else does.</p>

  <div class="card">
    <h4>1 · Parallel research subagents</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Ask Claude Code to "spawn 4 research agents to investigate each top-10 DSO competitor in parallel." You go make coffee. 10 minutes later, 4 detailed briefs in your folder. This is how the original competitor intel for this hub was generated.</p>
    <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Use case: every quarterly competitor refresh, every ICP deep-dive</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h4>2 · Filesystem-aware drafting</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Drop all your existing brand docs into a folder. Tell Claude Code "read everything in /clerri-brand, then draft a new product page that matches voice." It reads, internalizes, produces. Chat can't do this — file uploads are token-limited.</p>
    <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Use case: any draft that should match existing brand voice exactly</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h4>3 · Iterative refinement against test data</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Building workflow C (per-practice assets)? Export 10 real practice records as CSV. Tell Claude Code to read the CSV, generate 10 sample assets, eyeball results, refine the prompt until they're good. THEN hand the final prompt to n8n. Saves 5x the iteration time.</p>
    <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Use case: every workflow prompt before it goes into production</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h4>4 · Web research with persistence</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">"Find every dental influencer with &gt;10K LinkedIn followers, their content style, their sponsorship rates." Claude Code uses WebFetch + WebSearch + saves results to a markdown file. Hours of manual work → 20 min agentic flow.</p>
    <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Use case: ICP enrichment, partner discovery, market mapping</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h4>5 · Local data analysis</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Export Salesforce report as CSV. Drop it locally. "Analyze this for expansion patterns — which practice types grew enrollment fastest in Q4?" Claude Code reads pandas-style, surfaces patterns, generates Slack-ready summary.</p>
    <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Use case: any one-off data analysis you'd otherwise punt to BI team</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h4>6 · Persistent memory across sessions</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Claude Code can write to a memory folder. Tell it "remember that Clerri's brand voice avoids 'transform' and 'revolutionize.'" Next session, it remembers. Build a personal "marketing brain" over time.</p>
    <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Use case: your daily research+drafting environment</p>
  </div>

  <!-- WHAT YOU CAN DO WITHOUT BUDGET -->
  <h2>What you can do with <em>only Claude Code (no API spend).</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">If Jim hasn't approved tooling budget yet, Claude Code on your existing Pro/Max plan handles a surprising amount. Here's the realistic Day-1 workflow without spending anything on infrastructure.</p>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Daily ritual (30 min / day)</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>Morning: ask Claude Code to summarize yesterday's Becker's Dental + GDN headlines</li>
        <li>Generate the day's LinkedIn post for Jim's signature</li>
        <li>Draft 2-3 outreach emails to ICP targets, customized via Claude Code's web research</li>
        <li>Review Pardot engagement data, ask Claude Code to flag anomalies</li>
        <li>Capture meeting notes from 1:1s into a local folder; Claude Code synthesizes weekly</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Weekly tasks (2 hours / week)</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>Manual AEO check across 5 queries on ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude.ai</li>
        <li>Competitor LinkedIn review — Claude Code helps interpret what they're signaling</li>
        <li>Draft Friday team update email</li>
        <li>Prep Monday team standup agenda based on captured notes</li>
        <li>Research one ICP target in depth (decision-makers, recent news, warm intros)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Monthly artifacts</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>Charlesbank board update (Claude Code synthesizes month's wins + data)</li>
        <li>Competitor intel digest (manual research, Claude Code interprets)</li>
        <li>Content velocity review</li>
        <li>Quarterly planning kickoff doc</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>What you CAN'T do without API</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>Schedule autonomous workflows (need n8n + API)</li>
        <li>Personalize 5,000 assets in one job (need Batch API)</li>
        <li>Hand workflows to team members (each would need their own Claude Code)</li>
        <li>Real-time slash commands in Slack (need API + n8n)</li>
        <li>Sustained throughput at marketing-team scale</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- COST COMPARISON -->
  <h2>Cost comparison — <em>at realistic Clerri scale.</em></h2>
  <div class="callout">
    <div class="lbl">Marketing team of 4, ~6 months in</div>
    <table style="width:100%;margin-top:0.75rem">
      <thead><tr style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(207,252,120,0.3)"><th style="text-align:left;padding:0.5rem 0">Surface</th><th style="text-align:right;padding:0.5rem 0">Monthly cost</th><th style="text-align:left;padding-left:1rem">What you get</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem 0">Claude Pro (your seat)</td><td style="text-align:right;padding:0.5rem 0">$20</td><td style="padding-left:1rem">claude.ai for browser tasks</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem 0">Claude Code (you)</td><td style="text-align:right;padding:0.5rem 0">$0 incl. or pay-go</td><td style="padding-left:1rem">Daily research, drafting, agentic flows</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem 0">Claude Pro × 3 team seats</td><td style="text-align:right;padding:0.5rem 0">$60</td><td style="padding-left:1rem">Each marketer has their own</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem 0">Anthropic API (8 workflows running)</td><td style="text-align:right;padding:0.5rem 0">$300-600</td><td style="padding-left:1rem">All autonomous workflows from this hub</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem 0">n8n self-hosted</td><td style="text-align:right;padding:0.5rem 0">$7</td><td style="padding-left:1rem">Workflow orchestration</td></tr>
        <tr style="font-weight:700;border-top:1px solid rgba(207,252,120,0.3)"><td style="padding:0.5rem 0">Total Claude/AI infra</td><td style="text-align:right;padding:0.5rem 0">$390-690</td><td style="padding-left:1rem">Full team-scale operation</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Tasks</h2>
  <div data-section="claude-cli-vs-api">
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cli-01-claude-code-install" data-section="claude-cli-vs-api" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Install Claude Code locally + run your first agentic research session</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cli-02-projects-setup" data-section="claude-cli-vs-api" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Set up Claude.ai Projects for: brand voice, board updates, Charlesbank reporting</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cli-03-api-key" data-section="claude-cli-vs-api" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Get Anthropic API key + set spend cap ($500 alert / $1000 hard cap)</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cli-04-team-seats" data-section="claude-cli-vs-api" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Roll out Claude Pro/Max seats to marketing team (3 seats)</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cli-05-mcp-servers" data-section="claude-cli-vs-api" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Install MCP servers: HubSpot/Salesforce, Notion, Google Drive — connects Claude Code to your stack</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="cli-06-internal-doc" data-section="claude-cli-vs-api" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Document "when to use what" as internal one-pager for the team</div></div></label>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">CLI/API decisions notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="cli-vs-api" placeholder="What you've moved from chat to CLI to API, what surprised you, where each surface broke down..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/workflows"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">Workflow Recipes</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/martech-audit"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">Martech Audit</span></a>
  </div>

</div>
</ClerriLayout>
